<font color="#FF0000">REPLY TO BACSI</font><br>
<tt>Mon Nov 17 14:38:49 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Bacsi, I just gave my word to Marc Weiss, the webmaster of this thread, that I was not posting for awhile, due to the insane dog fight that was going on on later threads. I think he will forgive me this &quot;violation&quot; and answer.<br><br>
I did my two years of civilian &quot;service&quot; for the County of Los Angeles, Dept of Hospitals for first year, as a graveyard ob/gyn clear (really wierd for a guy) and then as a social worker for the Aid to Disabled Program with the Welfare Office. I drew a full salary as a county employee, but had to quarterly report to the draft board for supervision.  Nothing like being a combat medic or in the bush, I totally agree.<br><br>
Your comment about Kent State and CSN &amp; Y, or as we say in shrinkland, Freud, Marx, Engles, and Jung, was priceless.<br><br>
Where you served, or even if you got the C.O.status was totally subjective and at the whim of one's local draft board.  As I was quite &quot;outspoken&quot;, i.e. SDS and demostrations, let's just say my Board did not like me, and turned down my first 20 or 30 placement requests.  Finally, with legal intervention, we reached an accord, and off I went to Harbor General Hospital in Torrance Ca. Welfare and gang land, surrounded by oil refineries.  The air was dangerous at night, so was the parking lot. UCLA sent its interns there for training.<br><br>
As many of my posts have said, I do not consider myself a draft dodger, as I met my demon head on. I did not run to Canada, although I was tempted.  I happened to be in the Middle East in the summer of 1967 and saw what war was up close and personal, so to speak, and that shook up and yet reinforced my beliefs that war was wrong. Ah, to be so ideal and naive' again, now I am waiting for Saddam to get hit, and I am hopefull this time it will be total and complete.  Perhaps we do grow wiser with age, along with fatter.<br><br>
Hope to continue on talking with you.  (unless the &quot;pack&quot;) from the other threads finds us. If so, we can go to e mail.<br><br>
Barry
